1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:08,975
(Matthew 21:1): 'Jesus entered the temple of God and was casting out all those selling and buying [in the temple], etc.

2
00:00:08,925 --> 00:00:17,450
We read in the gospel that our Lord went into the temple and cast out all them that sold and bought and said to them that sold doves: ‘Take these things hence!

3
00:00:17,450 --> 00:00:25,587
It was his purpose to have the temple cleared, as though he said: This temple is by rights mine own and I want it to myself to be lord therein.

4
00:00:25,587 --> 00:00:34,525
This temple that God means to rule in is man’s soul which he has made exactly like himself, as saith the Lord, ‘We will make man in our image and likeness.

5
00:00:34,525 --> 00:00:35,812
Which he did.

6
00:00:35,812 --> 00:00:42,812
So like himself God made man’s soul that nothing else in earth or heaven resembles God so closely as the human soul.

7
00:00:42,812 --> 00:00:46,387
God wants this temple cleared of everything but himself.

8
00:00:46,387 --> 00:00:52,700
This is because this temple is so agreeable to him and he is so comfortable in this temple when he is there alone.

9
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:57,150
Now consider who they were that sold and bought therein and who they are still.

10
00:00:57,150 --> 00:01:00,400
Mark me well: I name none but the virtuous.

11
00:01:00,400 --> 00:01:09,750
Yet, even so, I can point out who the merchants were, and still are to this day, that thus buy and sell: those whom our Lord drove forth and cast out.

12
00:01:09,750 --> 00:01:15,475
He still does so to those that buy and sell in this temple: he would not leave a single one therein.

13
00:01:15,475 --> 00:01:33,200
Lo, they are merchants all who, while avoiding mortal sin and wishing to be virtuous, do good works to the glory of God, fasts, for example, vigils, prayers, etc., all of them excellent, but do them with a view to God’s giving them somewhat, doing to them somewhat, they wish for in return.

14
00:01:33,200 --> 00:01:35,087
All such are merchants.

15
00:01:35,087 --> 00:01:42,675
This is plain to see, for they reckon on giving one thing for another and so to barter with our Lord, though they are mistook as to the bargain.

16
00:01:42,675 --> 00:01:48,537
For all they have and have the power to do, they have from God and do effect by means of God alone.

17
00:01:48,537 --> 00:01:53,100
God has no call to do to them or give to them anything unless he choose to.

18
00:01:53,100 --> 00:01:58,425
For what they are they are from God and what they have they get from God, not from themselves.

19
00:01:58,425 --> 00:02:12,250
God is in no wise bounden to requite their acts or gifts, except he care to do so of his own free will, apart from what they do or give; for they give not of their own nor do they act of their own selves, as God says, ‘Without me ye can do nothing.

20
00:02:12,250 --> 00:02:17,812
They be sorry fools who bargain with our Lord like this; they know little or nothing of the truth.

21
00:02:17,812 --> 00:02:21,237
God cast them out of the temple and drove them forth.

22
00:02:21,237 --> 00:02:24,137
For light and darkness cannot dwell together.

23
00:02:24,137 --> 00:02:27,175
God is the truth, he is the light itself.

24
00:02:27,175 --> 00:02:33,475
When God enters the temple he drives out ignorance and darkness, revealing himself in the light of truth.

25
00:02:33,475 --> 00:02:37,950
Merchants go when the truth appears, for the truth needs no merchanting.

26
00:02:37,950 --> 00:02:43,725
God seeks not his own, he is perfectly free in all his acts, which he does in true love.

27
00:02:43,725 --> 00:02:55,325
So does the man who is at one with God: he is perfectly free in all his deeds; he does them out of love and without why, just to glorify God, not seeking his own therein, God energising in him.

28
00:02:55,325 --> 00:03:03,850
Moreover I maintain: as long as we work at all for gain, while we desire aught God may have given or may give, we rank with these merchants.

29
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:06,900
Wouldst thou be free from any taint of trade?

30
00:03:06,900 --> 00:03:13,700
then do what good thou canst and do it solely to God’s glory, as exempt from it thyself as though thou wert not.

31
00:03:13,700 --> 00:03:16,187
Ask nothing whatever in return.

32
00:03:16,187 --> 00:03:24,287
So done thy works are ghostly and godly; the merchants are driven from the temple and God is there alone when one has no intention but God.

33
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:27,025
Behold thy temple cleared of merchants.

34
00:03:27,025 --> 00:03:36,087
The man who is intent on God alone and on God’s glory, verily he is free from any taint of commerce in his deeds, nor is he in any wise self-seeking.

35
00:03:36,244 --> 00:03:41,719
I have related further how Jesus said to them that sold doves: ‘Take these things hence!

36
00:03:41,669 --> 00:03:48,231
These people he did not drive forth nor rebuke them harshly: he said quite mildly: ‘Take these things away!

37
00:03:48,231 --> 00:03:53,344
As though to say, it is not wrong albeit a hindrance to the pure and simple truth.

38
00:03:53,344 --> 00:04:01,906
These are virtuous folk, working for God impersonally though subject to personal limitations, to time and number, to before and after.

39
00:04:01,906 --> 00:04:20,356
Their activities keep them from the highest truth, from being absolutely free like our Lord Jesus Christ who is receiving himself afresh incessantly and a-temporally from his heavenly Father and in that same now is borne back again unceasingly with praise and thanksgiving into the Father, perfect, vieing with him in his majesty.

40
00:04:20,356 --> 00:04:38,744
Even so, to be receptive to the sovran truth, a man must be without before and after, without the hindrance of any acts or images that are within his ken, but freely receiving the divine gift in the perennial now and bearing it back unhindered in the light of the same with praise and thanksgiving in our Lord Jesus Christ.

41
00:04:38,744 --> 00:04:46,931
Then the doves are gone, to wit, the obstacle of ownership in actions, good in themselves, wherein one has any self-interest at all.

42
00:04:46,931 --> 00:04:52,794
Take these things hence!’ said our Lord, as though to say, they are blameless but they are in the way.

43
00:04:52,794 --> 00:05:07,194
When the temple is free from obstructions (possessions and strangers to wit), it looks right beautiful, shining out bright and clear above everything God has created and through everything God has created, so that none can compare with it but the uncreated God alone.

44
00:05:07,194 --> 00:05:12,219
In very truth, there is none like this temple but the uncreated God himself.

45
00:05:12,219 --> 00:05:15,819
Nothing below the angels is the least like this temple.

46
00:05:15,819 --> 00:05:22,156
The very highest angels are the same as this temple of the human soul in many ways, but not entirely.

47
00:05:22,156 --> 00:05:26,031
This partial likeness with the soul they have in love and knowledge.

48
00:05:26,031 --> 00:05:29,306
But there is a limit set them which they cannot pass.

49
00:05:29,306 --> 00:05:31,231
The soul goes on beyond.

50
00:05:31,231 --> 00:05:47,319
Suppose the soul to be identical with the highest human being here in time, nevertheless that man has the potential freedom to soar to untold heights above the angels in the now of each, new without number, that is, without mode: above the angelic mode and every created intelligence.

51
00:05:47,319 --> 00:05:54,381
God who alone is uncreated is her sole peer in freedom, though not in uncreatedness, for the soul is created.

52
00:05:54,381 --> 00:06:02,369
Emerging into the unclouded light she in her naught leaps so far into his naught that she is helpless to regain the state of her created aught.

53
00:06:02,369 --> 00:06:08,244
God with his uncreatedness supports her nothing-at-all, preserving the soul in his all-in-all.

54
00:06:08,244 --> 00:06:15,569
The soul has dared to come to naught and, failing by herself to reach herself, she swoons away ere God comes to her rescue.

55
00:06:15,569 --> 00:06:17,406
It must needs be so.

56
00:06:17,572 --> 00:06:25,847
Jesus, as I said, went into the temple and cast out them that bought and sold and he began to command the rest, ‘Take these things hence!

57
00:06:25,797 --> 00:06:31,272
The words I have here read, ‘Jesus went in and began to say, “Take these things hence!

58
00:06:31,272 --> 00:06:36,559
Observe, there was no one there but Jesus when he began to speak in the temple of the soul.

59
00:06:36,559 --> 00:06:48,597
Be sure of this: while anyone else is speaking in the temple (i.e, the soul) but Jesus, Jesus is silent, as though he were away, nor is he at home in the soul while she has strange guests to talk to.

60
00:06:48,597 --> 00:06:54,547
For Jesus to speak in the soul she must be all alone, and she has to be quiet to hear what he says.

61
00:06:54,547 --> 00:06:57,672
Well then, he comes in and starts speaking.

62
00:06:57,672 --> 00:06:59,284
What is it he says?

63
00:06:59,284 --> 00:07:00,984
He says what he is.

64
00:07:00,984 --> 00:07:02,734
What is he, then?

65
00:07:02,734 --> 00:07:04,709
He is the Word of the Father.

66
00:07:04,709 --> 00:07:14,959
In this same Word the Father speaks himself, all his divine nature, all that God is, just as he knows it, and he knows it as it is, for he is perfect in knowledge and power.

67
00:07:14,959 --> 00:07:17,997
It follows that he is perfect in speech too.

68
00:07:17,997 --> 00:07:45,997
In pronouncing the Word he utters himself and all things in another Person to whom he gives the nature that he has himself, and speaks all intelligences in echo of the actual Word, according to the indwelling image; like the sun-rays shining forth, so each (intelligence) is a word in itself, not the same in all respects as the Word, but: they have the power to receive by grace the same nature as the actual Word, and this Word as it is in itself the Father spoke entire by the Word and everything

69
00:07:45,997 --> 00:07:47,322
in that Word.

70
00:07:47,322 --> 00:07:51,634
If this is what the Father said, then what is Jesus saying in the soul?

71
00:07:51,634 --> 00:07:58,909
As I have told: the Father speaks his Word; he speaks in this Word and no otherwhere, and Jesus speaks in the soul.

72
00:07:58,909 --> 00:08:05,859
His manner of speaking is to reveal himself and what the Father said in him, so far as the soul is able to receive it.

73
00:08:05,859 --> 00:08:09,447
He reveals the Father in the soul in infinite power.

74
00:08:09,447 --> 00:08:28,834
Experiencing this power in the Son the soul waxes powerful in like emanation till she is the same in might and virtue and every perfection, so that neither joy nor sorrow nor aught that God has made in time avails to destroy that soul, she standing staunch as it were in this divine power against which all else is insignificant and futile.

75
00:08:28,834 --> 00:08:38,234
Secondly: Jesus reveals himself in the soul in infinite wisdom, himself to wit, the wisdom wherein the Father knows himself in full paternal power.

76
00:08:38,234 --> 00:08:45,022
The very Word, which is wisdom itself, and all that is therein, is, at the same time, one alone.

77
00:08:45,022 --> 00:08:56,497
When wisdom is in union with the soul, doubt, error and illusion are entirely removed, she is set in the bright pure light of God himself, as saith the prophet, ‘Lord in thy light shall we see light.

78
00:08:56,497 --> 00:09:02,584
Then God is known by God in the soul; she discerns with his wisdom both herself and all things.

79
00:09:02,584 --> 00:09:12,472
She knows not this same wisdom with herself, but with this wisdom she discerns the Father fruitful in travail and his real being in impartible oneness void of all distinctions.

80
00:09:12,472 --> 00:09:18,434
Jesus manifests himself further in infinite suavity and fullness in all receptive hearts.

81
00:09:18,434 --> 00:09:32,072
When Jesus reveals himself in this plenitude of sweetness, uniting with the soul, then on this amiable tide the soul floats into herself and out of herself and beyond the things of grace, back in unmitigated power into her first source.

82
00:09:32,072 --> 00:09:39,572
Thus the outward man is obedient, even unto death, to the inner man now established in peace in the service of God for ever.

83
00:09:39,572 --> 00:09:48,272
May Jesus enter into us and clear out and cast away all hindrances of soul and body to the end that we are one with him here upon earth and there in heaven.

84
00:09:48,272 --> 00:09:49,934
So help us God.

85
00:09:49,934 --> 00:09:50,884
Amen.
